#  Python Digital Clock (Tkinter)

##  Overview

This project is a simple digital clock application developed using Python. It uses the Tkinter library to create a graphical user interface (GUI) that displays the current time and date.

##  How It Works

The program creates a window where the current time and date are shown. The time is displayed in 12-hour format with AM/PM, and the date shows the day, date, month, and year.

The application updates itself every second using a built-in function, ensuring that the displayed time is always accurate and real-time.

##  Concept Used

* GUI development using Tkinter
* Time formatting using strftime
* Date handling using datetime
* Real-time updating using loop scheduling

##  Purpose

The purpose of this project is to practice Python programming and understand how real-time applications and graphical interfaces work.

##  Summary

This is a beginner-friendly project that demonstrates how Python can be used to build simple yet useful desktop applications.

